*September 14 – [[Servílio Conti]], 97, Italian-born Brazilian Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Roraima|Roraima]] (1965–1975).<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcontis.html Bishop Servílio Conti]</ref>
*September 30 – [[Jadir Ambrósio]], 91, Brazilian musician and composer.<ref>[http://www.otempo.com.br/superfc/aos-91-anos-morre-o-compositor-do-hino-do-cruzeiro-jadir-ambr%C3%B3sio-1.924050 Aos 91 anos, morre o compositor do hino do Cruzeiro Jadir Ambrósio] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*October 3 – [[Lori Sandri]], 65, Brazilian football manager, brain tumor.<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/pr/noticia/2014/10/ex-treinador-lori-sandri-morre-aos-65-anos-em-curitiba.html Lori Sandri morre aos 65 anos em Curitiba, vítima de tumor cerebral] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*October 4 – [[Hugo Carvana]], 77, Brazilian actor (''[[Entranced Earth]]'', ''[[Antonio das Mortes]]'') and director (''[[Casa da Mãe Joana]]'').<ref>[http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/noticias/noticia/2014/10/morre-o-ator-hugo-carvana-4613776.html Morre o ator Hugo Carvana] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*October 15 – [[João Corso]], 86, Brazilian Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Campos|Campos]] (1990–1995).<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcorso.html Bishop João Corso, S.D.B.]</ref>
*November 1 – [[Edson Décimo Alves Araújo]], 27, Brazilian footballer ([[Clube Atlético Paranaense|Atlético-PR]]), shot.<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/pi/noticia/2014/11/em-ultima-gravacao-edson-piaui-deixa-recado-criancas-futuro-decente.html Em última gravação, Edson Piauí deixa recado a crianças: "Futuro decente"] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*November 1 – [[Alberto Johannes Först]], 87, German-born Brazilian Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dourados|Dourados]] (1990–2001).<ref>[http://www.katholisch.de/de/katholisch/themen/news/page_news.php?id=42204 Ehemaliger brasilianischer Bischof verstorben] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102154454/http://www.katholisch.de/de/katholisch/themen/news/page_news.php?id=42204 |date=2014-11-02 }} {{de icon}}</ref>
*November 11 – [[Caetano Lima dos Santos]], 98, Brazilian bishop of the Roman Catholic Church.<ref>[http://catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/blids.html (Layman) Caetano Antônio Lima dos Santos, O.F.M. Cap. †]</ref>
*November 13 – [[Manoel de Barros]], 97, Brazilian poet.<ref>[http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2014/11/1547466-morre-o-poeta-mato-grossense-manoel-de-barros-97.shtml Morre o poeta mato-grossense Manoel de Barros, aos 97 anos] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*November 14 – [[Adib Jatene]], 85, Brazilian cardiologist and politician, [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Minister of Health]] (1992, 1995–1996), heart attack.<ref>[http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/health/2014/11/15/famous-brazilian-cardiologist-and-ex-health-minister-adib-jatene-dies/ Famous Brazilian cardiologist and ex-health minister Adib Jatene dies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303232739/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/health/2014/11/15/famous-brazilian-cardiologist-and-ex-health-minister-adib-jatene-dies/ |date=2016-03-03 }}</ref>
*November 20 – [[Márcio Thomaz Bastos]], 79, Brazilian politician, [[Ministry of Justice (Brazil)|Minister of Justice]] (2003–2007), lung failure.<ref>[http://g1.globo.com/sao-paulo/noticia/2014/11/morre-em-sao-paulo-o-ex-ministro-da-justica-marcio-thomaz-bastos.html Morre em São Paulo o ex-ministro da Justiça Márcio Thomaz Bastos] {{pt icon}}</ref>
*November 20 – [[Samuel Klein (businessman)|Samuel Klein]], 91, Polish-born Brazilian magnate ([[Casas Bahia]]).<ref>[http://www.laprensasa.com/309_america-in-english/2805229_samuel-klein-founder-of-brazil-s-largest-appliance-chain-dies.html Samuel Klein, founder of Brazil's largest appliance chain, dies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052312/http://www.laprensasa.com/309_america-in-english/2805229_samuel-klein-founder-of-brazil-s-largest-appliance-chain-dies.html |date=2016-03-04 }}</ref>
*December 3 – [[Alfredo Ernest Novak]], 84, American-born Brazilian Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Paranaguá|Paranaguá]] (1989–2006).<ref>[http://catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bnovak.html Bishop Alfredo Ernest Novak]</ref>
*December 9 – [[José Feghali]], 53, Brazilian pianist, suicide by gunshot.<ref>[http://keranews.org/post/cliburn-piano-winner-and-tcu-professor-jos-feghali-has-died Cliburn Piano Winner And TCU Professor José Feghali Has Died]</ref>
